title: Labor's hate speech bill has been ‘horribly rushed’
description: Shadow Fisheries and Forestry Minister Ross Cadell criticises the Labor Party for a rushed Bill.  “The prime minister called us back with a bill that was not going to be split and was not going to be changed,” Mr Cadell told Sky News Australia.  “It ended up being both of those things in a rushed and a horrible way.   “We didn’t believe as a party and myself individually that there was enough certainty around the protections for the group we weren’t trying to target.”

title: New Zealand general election to be held on November 7
description: New Zealand Prime Minister Christopher Luxon has announced the date for the 2026 election.  The New Zealand general election is to be held on Saturday, November 7, 2026.  “Kiwis can have great certainty that over the coming year, our government will continue working incredibly hard,” Mr Luxon said.

title: Zohran Mamdani fully supports ‘abolishing ICE’ as Democrats continue attacks against agency
description: New York City Mayor Zohran Mamdani has declared he is in full support of “abolishing ICE” as the agency ramps up its immigration crackdown.  “I am in support of abolishing ICE, and I’ll tell you why. Because what we see is an entity that has no interest in fulfilling its stated reason to exist,” Mamdani said.  “We’re seeing a government agency that is supposed to be enforcing some kind of an immigration law, but instead, what it’s doing is terrorising people, no matter their immigration status, no matter the facts of the law, no matter the facts of the case.”  Mamdani’s scathing remarks came during an appearance on ‘The View’ on Tuesday, arguing he is “tired” of seeing agents dragging people “out of their life”.  “What we need to see is humanity, and there is a way to care about immigration in this city and in this country with a sense of humanity,” Mamdani said.

title: ‘Who would vote for that garbage?’: Barnaby Joyce unleashes on Labor’s hate laws
description: One Nation MP Barnaby Joyce claims Labor’s hate laws passed by the House are “censorship” laws.  “We are in a pen of legislation, which at its most aggravated form, it’s up to 15 years in jail,” Mr Joyce told Sky News Australia.  “Who would vote for that garbage?”

title: Trump acquiring Greenland is ‘truly inconceivable’
description: Democrat Lobbyist Nathan Daschle believes the idea of US President Donald Trump invading Greenland is inconceivable.  “When we built Nato, we never contemplated what would happen if one NATO ally attacks or invades another,” Mr Daschle told Sky News Australia.   “This is truly inconceivable.  “Most Americans are absolutely furious with this idea.”

title: Trump’s lawyers would be ‘very unhappy’ if he tried to speak to Maduro in prison
description: US President Donald Trump says he will not visit Nicolas Maduro in prison to question him on Venezuela's alleged tampering in elections.  “No, I don't think I’ll be doing that, I think my lawyers would be very unhappy,” Mr Trump said.  “They've learned some things.”

title: ‘I saved millions of people’: Trump responds to Nobel Peace Prize loss
description: US President Donald Trump claims the Nobel Peace Prize “wouldn't improve" American lives, but insists he improved the lives of people living in war-ridden countries.  "I saved probably tens of millions of lives in the wars," Mr Trump said.  “When you look at India and Pakistan, that could have been 10, 15, 20 million people.  "I saved millions of people. So that to me is the big thing." ​

title: Barnaby Joyce would ‘welcome’ more Nationals defecting to One Nation
description: One Nation MP Barnaby Joyce claims he would “of course” welcome further Nationals defecting to One Nation.  Mr Joyce told Sky News Australia that leaving a political party is “very similar” to having a divorce.  “This is an incredibly personal decision, and you’ll make it on your own.”

title: ‘Nobody has done more for Nato than I have’: Tensions arise between Trump and NATO
description: US President Donald Trump discusses whether the possible breakup of a NATO alliance is the price he is willing to pay for Greenland.  Mr Trump references his success in getting NATO countries to commit to spending up to “5 per cent of GDP” on defence.  "Nobody has done more for NATO than I have, in every way.  “NATO is going to be happy, and we are going to be very happy.  “If NATO doesn't have us, NATO is not very strong.”

title: Brooklyn Beckham has ‘completely and utterly trashed’ his reputation following public rant
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand claims Brooklyn Beckham has “completely and utterly trashed” his reputation following his comments about his parents in recent social media posts.  “Brooklyn has shown he absolutely in no way gives any consideration to the brand,” he said.  “Because he has just completely and utterly trashed his ... reputation.”

title: ‘Boohoo, go cry’: ‘Spoilt brat’ Brooklyn Beckham brutally savaged following ‘nuclear’ rant
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio claims “entitled” Brooklyn Beckham has gone “nuclear” following his lengthy statement in which he claimed he didn’t want to reconcile with his family and made accusations against his parents.  “Firstly, he’s gone nuclear, alright? Prince Harry 2.0 ladies and gentlemen has rocked up,” she said.  “The guy’s an absolute spoilt twat in my opinion.  “The guy is a spoilt brat.  “Oh boohoo, go cry, go find a job, there are bigger problems out there for goodness sake.”

title: ‘Prince Harry 2.0 ladies and gentlemen’: Brooklyn Beckham’s claims debunked and exposed
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio has analysed Brooklyn Beckham’s lengthy statement making accusations against his parents.  “I’m going to take you through some of the statement and why he’s acting so entitled,” she said.  “Firstly, this was one of the quotes, ‘my mum cancelled making Nicola’s dress’ – this was at the wedding – ‘in the 11th hour despite how excited she was to wear her design, forcing her to urgently find a new dress’.  “Well, that’s already been debunked.”

title: Trump’s top three accomplishments in first year back in office
description: US President Donald Trump states his top three accomplishments were rebuilding the military, sealing business deals and investments, and achieving most-favoured-nation pricing for prescription drugs.  “The building of a really powerful military has been a great achievement. That would include the Venezuela thing, and the attack on Iran, the wiping out of the nuclear threat,” Mr Trump said.  “What we've done in business has been incredible; we have $18 trillion coming in.  “Our drug prices are going to come down to numbers never even seen before.”

title: Greenland citizens ‘concerned’ over an ‘unimaginable’ US invasion
description: CNN International Diplomatic Editor Nic Robertson raises Greenland citizens' concerns over a US invasion.  “The United States sent in troops yesterday, along with Canadian troops, to their space base,” Mr Robertson told Sky News Australia.   “If they were to come with force and fire upon Danish troops whose presence here has been increased over the last few days, the Danish troops are obligated through their constitution to defend the Kingdom of Denmark.  “The scenarios are unimaginable.  “The concern here is real.  “The people are concerned here.”

title: Trump ‘might’ replace United Nations with Board of Peace
description: US President Donald Trump claims the Board of Peace "might" replace the United Nations.  “The UN just hasn't been very helpful,” Mr Trump said.  “I'm a big fan of the UN potential. But it has never lived up to its potential.  “The UN should have settled every one of the wars that I settled.”
